@startuml repair_oracle_loop
' Diagram 5/5 — the repair/oracle loop: how a red gate becomes a fix.
' Source of truth: scripts/run_phased.py (--rerun-task, reevaluate_phase_gate),
' oracle_records_for_phase, build_repair_description, repair-task-template.md.

skinparam shadowing false

start
:Phase gate RED\n(per-predicate outcomes recorded);
:Resolve oracle: oracle_records_for_phase\nreads tasks.jsonl, LATEST record wins\n(mechanical re-evals are persisted too — **F17b**);
note right
  oracle quality is bounded by what
  gates can NAME (**F7**) and by what
  artifacts let surface: swallowed
  errors starve the oracle (**F17**);
  captures keep head+tail so pytest's
  tail summary survives (**F11**)
end note
:Build repair prompt =\noriginal task description\n+ AUTHORITY clause\n+ oracle VERBATIM;
note right
  repair inherits the original task's
  context (**F9**) — so the original
  description must carry the contract
  (**F8**), and the authority clause
  states the tests/spec are right
end note
:--rerun-task <task> --oracle <phase>\n(cross-phase allowed: fix lives in\nanother phase's artifact);
:Task executes; its OWN gate must be\nable to red on its own defect (**F10**)\n— a locally-green task no-ops under\na foreign oracle;
:reevaluate_phase_gate — mechanical,\nfull gate re-evaluated (**F23**),\nrecord marked mechanical: true;
if (gate green?) then (yes)
  :continue (--next);
  stop
else (no)
  if (conditions defect verified?\n(framework bug / channel\nstarvation / spec defect)) then (yes)
    :re-establish WITHOUT consuming\nbudget (standing rule, 3 precedents);
    stop
  else (no)
    :budget: ONE repair per gate;\nsecond red on the same gate\nSTOPS THE RUN — waivers forbidden;
    stop
  endif
endif
@enduml
